# 🛢️ OilyGiant Oil Well Selection — Profit & Risk Analysis

## Overview

Drilling an oil well costs millions. Choosing the wrong region can mean catastrophic losses. This project builds a data-driven framework to help **OilyGiant** — a fictional oil extraction company — identify which of three candidate regions offers the best combination of expected profit and acceptable financial risk.

Using linear regression to predict oil reserves and bootstrap sampling to simulate profit distributions, this project delivers a clear, defensible recommendation backed by statistical evidence.

---

## 📌 Problem Statement

OilyGiant has geological survey data from three regions. The challenge: **select the single best region** to develop 200 new oil wells, maximizing expected profit while keeping the probability of a loss below 2.5%.

This is a real-world optimization problem — not just which region looks best on average, but which one is the smartest bet when risk is factored in.

---

## 🔍 Key Findings & Insights

| Metric | Region 0 | Region 1 | Region 2 |
|--------|----------|----------|----------|
| Dataset size | 100,000 wells | 100,000 wells | 100,000 wells |
| Mean actual volume | 92.50 k/bbl | 68.83 k/bbl | 95.00 k/bbl |
| Model RMSE | 37.76 | **0.89** | 40.15 |
| Mean predicted volume | 92.40 k/bbl | 68.71 k/bbl | 94.77 k/bbl |
| Mean profit (bootstrap) | $4,133,525 | **$4,354,227** | $3,890,054 |
| 95% Confidence Interval | (-$944K, $9.3M) | **($387K, $8.4M)** | (-$993K, $8.9M) |
| Loss probability | 4.50% | **1.40%** | 6.60% |
| **Recommended?** | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |

- **Region 1 is the clear recommendation** — it is the only region with a loss probability below the 2.5% threshold, and its entire 95% confidence interval is above zero.
- Region 1's model achieved an extraordinarily low RMSE of **0.89**, indicating a near-perfect linear relationship between its geological features and reserve volume — making predictions highly reliable.
- Regions 0 and 2 both carry unacceptable risk: loss probabilities of 4.50% and 6.60% respectively, with confidence intervals dipping well below break-even.
- Despite Region 2 having the highest mean actual volume (95.00 k/bbl), its high prediction error makes it too unreliable to select confidently.
- This analysis demonstrates why **expected value alone is insufficient** for capital-intensive decisions — variance and downside risk must always be quantified.

